author: ANDRE WRIGHT
title: Jaguars’ offense clicks in loss at Wicksburg
text:
Jaguars’ offense clicks in loss at Wicksburg ANDRE WRIGHT dothaneagle.com 
WICKSBURG – Barbour County erupted for a season-high 34 points, but that wasn’t enough as the Wicksburg Panthers scored a season-high of their own in a 58-34 victory Friday night at Panther Stadium. 
Wicksburg improved to 6-3 overall and 3-3 in Class 3A, Region 2 play. Barbour County dropped to 0-9 and 0-5. Wicksburg will be the region’s No. 4 seed and will travel to Gordo for their first-round game. Barbour County will play its final regular season game on Friday at home as Slocomb comes to Clayton. 
Wicksburg got off to a fast start and led 36-12 by halftime. Quarterback Tucker Driskell threw for two touchdowns and added one rushing, while five players scored at least once for the Panthers. 
Barbour County had little trouble scoring, but had much trouble stopping Wicksburg. BCHS quarterback Dywaun Walton had a big night, throwing for four touchdowns and running for another. 
In the first quarter, Walton connected with Kenneth Hunter, Jr for a 30-yard touchdown pass and Michael Curry caught a deflected ball off the fingertips of Marquell Jones and ran in from 30 yards out. 
In the third quarter, Walton scored on a 20-yard run, and Jones added the two-point conversion to cut the Wicksburg lead to 43-20. 
Walton would toss two more TD passes in the fourth period – 20 yards to Jaylin Robinson and 40 yards to Jaquvius Richardson. Jones added another two-point conversion for the final margin. 
Deondre McClain, Kevarion Pugh, Decourious Rodgers and Miezan Upshaw each played well for the Jaguars on defense. 
Friday will be Senior Night for the Jaguars as Slocomb (5-3, 3-2) visits. Kickoff is set for 7 p.m.
